<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 11 at 4:05AM CST  by NWS Hastings</headline>
<description>...Near Critical Fire Weather Conditions Likely This Afternoon...
Although relative humidity values this afternoon are not expected
to officially meet critical fire weather thresholds that would
necessitate issuance of a formal Warning, solidly near-critical
conditions are likely. This will be due to the combination of
north-northwest winds gusting as high as 40 to 45 MPH and relative
humidity dropping as low as 25 to 30 percent.
As a result, and despite the absence of a formal Warning, caution
is advised across the area this afternoon if engaging in any
activity that could spark a fire, as fires could spread somewhat
aggressively.</description>
